Christie is an organisation development and human capital professional, with nine years of experience collaborating with large national and global organizations on their transformation initiatives, including organizational assessments, strategic communications, service delivery, organizational alignment, and program management.

As a recent cancer survivor, Christie is using her strategy, technology, and healthcare experience to develop tools that empower patients during treatment and provide medical teams with real-time patient data that help improve patients' outcomes and quality of life.

Christie is also an expert facilitator with experience in stakeholder engagement, communications, large-scale event facilitation, and leadership development. She has her MS in Organization Development and has worked in the United States and South Africa. She has delivered strategy, technology, organization development, and human capital support to clients such as World Bank Group, U.S. Customs and Border Protection, U.S. Department of Homeland Security, U.S. Department of Navy, and U.S. Postal Service.
